19/11/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The chiefs of staff from Bulgaria, Greece, Romania and Turkey met in Bucharest on Monday (18 November), the second such get-together. 
The officials from Greece and Turkey, Georgios Antonakopoulos and Hilmi Ozkok, assured their Bulgarian and Romanian counterparts, Nikola Kolev and Mihail Popescu, of their countries' firm support for the Romanian and Bulgarian bids for NATO membership. 
The chiefs of staff noted the positive influence co-operation among the four armies has had in building confidence, security and stability in Southeast Europe. 
(Rompres - 18/11/02)
